  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For cases paired with matched germline controls, germline variants were filtered out if present in the matched germline sample.",
    "For unpaired cases, possible germline variants were filtered and classified as for somatic mutation calling from RNA-seq.",
    "The counting of somatic mutations included all the pathogenic or likely pathogenic mutations detected by WGS, whereas mutation detection from cases with only RNA-seq data is limited to the 87 preselected genes.",
    "SVs were analyzed using CREST (Clipping REveals STructure) 85 (v.1.0), and CNVs were analyzed using CONSERTING 86 on the WGS data.",
    "CNVs were also called on cases with only WES DNA data using the following methods."
  ],
